Biotin does not help hair grow. It's a B6 that turns food into energy. If your hair is falling out in clumps, check your iron levels. Women are prone to low iron due to our mentral cycle. If you're pale, sometimes has dizziness, tiredness.... it's your iron. Iron from meat stored better in the body and you may need a supplement. Taking b vitamins just gives you energy, which masks your actual problem. If you are going to take B vitamins, take a B-complex so you don't break out.
